The paper presents an algorithm for learning mixed membership models, which is a topic in machine learning and statistics. The algorithm reduces computational complexity and addresses the issue of negative entries in empirical estimators. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves some information theory concepts, which could make it relevant to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
